The paper discusses the concept of service shifting in the context of network orchestration and 5G architectures, which involves managing virtual network functions (VNFs) to provide services. This topic is closely related to computer networks (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY), as well as distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and benefits of service shifting, which could involve security and cryptography (cs.CR) and architecture (cs.AR).
